MCEM iterations for inference on the parameters of an OU process with unit
 diffusion given the joint distribution at 
\begin_inset Formula $t=\{0,1\}$
\end_inset

 induced by a solution to 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:ou-sde"

\end_inset

 with various initial conditions and 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda=1,\mu=0$
\end_inset

, using approximate and exact generalized bridge samplers.
 The 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

th iteration is performed using 
\begin_inset Formula $100\times\left\lfloor i^{1.5}\right\rfloor $
\end_inset

 MC samples, and the Fletcher-Reeves conjugate gradient method is used for
 maximization.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Of course, as noted in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "chap:EM"

\end_inset

, diffusions with unit diffusion coefficient are far too restrictive of
 a class of processes to focus on.
 As an example of diffusions with arbitrary coefficient, we consider solutions
 to 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:cir-sde"

\end_inset

.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta=(\lambda,\mu,\sigma)$
\end_inset

, we may follow 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:lamperti"

\end_inset

 to define a diffusion 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

, which is a Lamperti transformation of 
\begin_inset Formula $C$
\end_inset

, by writing
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Y_{t}=\eta_{\theta}(C_{t})=\frac{2\sqrt{C_{t}}}{\sigma},
\]

\end_inset

 so that 
\begin_inset Formula $\eta_{\theta}^{-1}(Y_{t})=\frac{\sigma^{2}}{4}Y_{t}^{2}$
\end_inset

.
 By 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:eta-y"

\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

 is the solution to the SDE 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
dY_{t}=\left(-\frac{\lambda Y_{t}}{2}-\frac{1}{2Y_{t}}\left(1-\frac{4\lambda\mu}{\sigma^{2}}\right)\right)dt+dW_{t},
\]

\end_inset

for a Wiener process 
\begin_inset Formula $W_{t}$
\end_inset

.
 Then, the necessary expressions to carry out MCEM according to 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:general-q"

\end_inset

 are
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
s_{\theta}(x) & = & \frac{-\lambda(x-\mu\log x)}{\sigma^{2}}\\
g_{\theta}(x) & = & \frac{-\lambda(x-\mu\log x)\left(\log\sigma+\frac{1}{2}\log x\right)}{2\sigma^{2}}
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
A_{\theta}(Y_{t}) & = & -\frac{\lambda Y_{t}^{2}}{4}-\left(\frac{1}{2}-\frac{2\lambda\mu}{\sigma^{2}}\right)\log Y_{t},\mbox{ and}\\
(\alpha_{\theta}^{2}+\alpha'_{\theta})(Y_{t}) & = & \left(-\frac{\lambda Y_{t}}{2}-\frac{1}{2Y_{t}}\left(1-\frac{4\lambda\mu}{\sigma^{2}}\right)\right)^{2}-\frac{\lambda}{2}+\frac{1}{2Y_{t}^{2}}\left(1-\frac{4\lambda\mu}{\sigma^{2}}\right).
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset


